    <text type="petition">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01007.001.jpg"/>
                        
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">                
                                
                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">                   
                
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName> Clerk of the Circuit Court for the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName></salute>
                        <salute>Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    
                    <p><persName>John Warren</persName> of <placeName>Washn DC</placeName> having claim to service or labor of the undersigned and having refused or neglected to file in your office the statement in writing or Schedule provided for in the 9th Section of the Act of Congress Entitled "An Act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>" approved <date when="1862-04-16">April 16th 1862</date>,</p>
                    <p>You will please file and record in your office the annexed Schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act approved <date when="1862-07-12">July 12th 1862</date>. The Said <persName>Maria Warren</persName> was resident of the Said <placeName>District</placeName> on the <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date>, and had been for Seven years previous.</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>height</cell>
                            <cell>Remarks</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Maria Warren</persName></cell>
                            <cell><choice><abbr>abt</abbr><expan>about</expan></choice> 55 <choice><abbr>yrs</abbr><expan>years</expan></choice></cell>
                            <cell>female</cell>
                            <cell>5 ft ½ in</cell>
                            <cell>Dark color</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Maria Warren</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness
                        <signed><persName>Tho. J. Fisher</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01007.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>50<choice><abbr>c</abbr><expan>cents</expan></choice></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><persName>Maria Warren</persName></ab>
                        <ab>schedule Amended Act</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folio 103</ab>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                            <ab><choice><abbr>Cert</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> given <choice><abbr>Idfd</abbr><expan>Identified</expan></choice> by <persName>T. J. Fisher</persName></ab>
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-08-16">August 16th 1862</date></ab>                                               
                    </div3>  
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <p>The Commissioners, satisfied on the testimony of <persName>Thomas J. Fisher</persName>, of the truth of the within statement, order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-08-16">Aug. 16, 1862</date></dateline>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                Clerk to Commissioners
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01007.005.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="billofsale" subtype="handwritten">
                    <dateline><placeName>Washington City</placeName> <date when="1855-12-23">23 Decr 1855</date></dateline>
                    <p>For and in consideration of the Sum of three hundred &amp; fifty two Dollars to me in hand paid by <persName>John Warren</persName>, I hereby Sell &amp; assign to the Said <persName>John Warren</persName> all my right title &amp; interest in &amp; to <persName>Maria Warren</persName> wife of the Said <persName>John</persName>.</p>
                    <ab>$352</ab>
                    <closer>
                        <signed><persName>Wm. Thos. Carroll</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness
                        <signed><persName>Tho. J. Fisher</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>
            </div1>
            
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf003r" facs="cww.01007.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="mixed">
                <dateline><seg type="handwritten"><date when="1862-08-16">Augt 16</date>.</seg></dateline>
                <div2 type="procedural" subtype="handwritten">
                    <ab><persName>Maria Warren</persName></ab>
                    <ab>Servant of <persName>John Warren</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony" subtype="handwritten">
                    <p><persName>Thomas J. Fisher</persName>. I know this servant and know she was servant of <persName>Wm. Thomas Carroll</persName> and sold by him to <persName>John Warren</persName> as appears by bill of sale. I loaned <persName>Warren</persName> money to purchase her. She was here <date when="1862-04-16">16 April 1862</date> and since and for years before with owners consent.</p>
                </div2>     
                
                <div2 type="procedural" subtype="handwritten">
                <ab><choice><abbr>cert</abbr><expan>certificate</expan></choice> ordered</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="cww.01007.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="mixed">
                    <div3 type="section" subtype="handwritten">
                        <ab><persName>Maria Warren</persName></ab>
                        <ab><date when="1862-09-02">August 16</date>.</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section" subtype="handwritten">
                        <ab><date when="1862-09-02">Aug 16</date>.</ab>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Office of the Commissioners under the act of <date when="1862-04-16">April 16, 1862</date>, entitled, "An act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>,"</ab>
                        <ab>City Hall, <placeName>Washington City, D. C.</placeName> <space atLeast="1"/>, <date when="1862">1862</date>.</ab> 
                        <ab><seg type="handwritten">187</seg></ab>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
                
                
            </div1>            
        </body>
    </text>
